<small id="desc">basic scryfall search syntax</small>

<!-- Content -->
<h2>Basics of Searching</h2>
<p>Here are some basic ways you can search for cards on Plainstext using simple queries. Below are a few key search fields and examples.</p>

<h3>Search by Card Name</h3>
<p>Just type the name of the card to search for it:</p>
<code>name:"Llanowar Elves"</code>
<code>name:"Lightning Bolt"</code>

<h3>Search by Mana Cost</h3>
<p>Filter by specific mana costs using the mana symbols in curly braces:</p>
<code>mana={G}</code> <!-- Green mana -->
<code>mana={1}{W}</code> <!-- 1 colorless and 1 white mana -->

<h3>Search by Type</h3>
<p>Search for cards by their type. You can use full types like "Creature," or more specific subtypes:</p>
<code>type:Creature</code>
<code>type:"Elf Druid"</code>

<h3>Search by Rarity</h3>
<p>Find cards by their rarity level:</p>
<code>rarity:common</code>
<code>rarity:rare</code>

<h3>Search by Set</h3>
<p>Find cards in a specific set by using the set code:</p>
<code>set:lea</code> <!-- Limited Edition Alpha -->
<code>set:m21</code> <!-- Core Set 2021 -->

<h3>Search by Color</h3>
<p>You can search by card colors. Use the color abbreviations: W (white), U (blue), B (black), R (red), G (green):</p>
<code>color:red</code>
<code>color:white</code>

<h3>Combined Search Examples</h3>
<p>You can combine multiple queries to narrow your results:</p>
<code>name:"Savannah Lions" type:Creature</code>
<code>mana={B} type:Creature rarity:common</code>

<!-- Fun sample queries -->
<h2>Fun Sample Queries</h2>
<ul>
    <li><a href="?cmc<3 type:instant color:red" target="_blank">Burn spells under 3 CMC</a></li>
    <li><a href="?mana={B} type:creature rarity:common" target="_blank">Common Black Creatures</a></li>
    <li><a href="?set:m21 rarity:rare" target="_blank">Rare cards from M21</a></li>
    <li><a href="?name:lightning color:red" target="_blank">Red cards with "Lightning" in the name</a></li>
</ul>

